{"TopicId":175422,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"StarMods: Advanced Fly-By-Wire Revived!","CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-28T20:00:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-28T20:00:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cfigure class=\u0022tmblr-full\u0022 data-orig-height=\u0022184\u0022 data-orig-width=\u00221008\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://78.media.tumblr.com/023309c59f9778bbc9e3c5eaaaa1d588/tumblr_inline_p9g66vcLfP1rr2wit_540.png\u0022 data-orig-height=\u0022184\u0022 data-orig-width=\u00221008\u0022 alt=\u0022tumblr_inline_p9g66vcLfP1rr2wit_540.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003Cfigure class=\u0022tmblr-full\u0022 data-orig-height=\u0022897\u0022 data-orig-width=\u00221517\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://78.media.tumblr.com/8b514f45a9e38342f993f4b1ffbc9f0f/tumblr_inline_p9g67jFr8t1rr2wit_540.png\u0022 data-orig-height=\u0022897\u0022 data-orig-width=\u00221517\u0022 alt=\u0022tumblr_inline_p9g67jFr8t1rr2wit_540.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://goo.gl/wcv35Q\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\nThis mod\u003C/a\u003E gives you a wonderful interface to improve the controller handling of #KSP! \u003Cbr\u003EBy Linuxgurugamer\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-29T09:27:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice pick, it\u0027s a great mod. Wish we\u0027d not need it though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Thomot512","CreatedById":156899,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-30T08:36:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223388373\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527586072\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dafni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Dafni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice pick, it\u0027s a great mod. Wish we\u0027d not need it though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotally agree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cfds","CreatedById":82109,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T09:22:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother fine example of SQUAD outsourcing core features to the community and somehow being proud of it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T09:56:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223387995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527537625\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266485\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SQUAD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/29/2018 at 8:00 AM, SQUAD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://goo.gl/wcv35Q\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis mod\u003C/a\u003E gives you a wonderful interface to improve the controller handling of #KSP!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd if you run GNU/Linux, odds are it\u0027s currently the only way to have a working controller \u003Cem\u003Eat all\u003C/em\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlease fix stock input handling, so that this mod can continue to be an optional and awesome extension, rather than another embarrassing case of the modding community leaving you for dust and small pebbles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223392464\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528104125\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002282109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cfds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, cfds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother fine example of SQUAD outsourcing core features to the community and somehow being proud of it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah... and bugfixes too, apparently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-04T09:57:36Z\u0022 title=\u002206/04/2018 09:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 4, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EQuoting is still broken...\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T11:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad to see the irony is not lost on the community.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-05T03:52:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr, you guys could be saying,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations on the popularity of your mod, Linuxgurugamer! It is greatly appreciated. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ringerc","CreatedById":128140,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T13:06:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuge thanks for this. After wrestling jstest and /dev/input/js0, SDL environment variables and more and simply being unable to make KSP see my joystick ... magic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nImagine, if the core game ... used SDL. Which makes joysticks easy. Unless you break it completely... somehow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven better the breakage is silent. KSP doesn\u0027t appear to attempt to find the joystick at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSearch hints:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP joystick environment variable SDL SDL2\u00A0SDL_HINT_GAMECONTROLLERCONFIG ksp joystick not detected ksp joystick not working afbw advanced by by wire oh my god just fix the bug\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"noahjudy","CreatedById":201442,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-17T07:41:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI copied files and pasted them into the kerbal space program file (i have steam) but i dont see a controller icon during flight\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-17T09:19:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223706294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221573976492\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201442\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022noahjudy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, noahjudy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI copied files and pasted them into the kerbal space program file (i have steam) but i dont see a controller icon during flight\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be a question to ask in the mod thread \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"noahjudy","CreatedById":201442,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-17T20:35:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason my presets aren\u2019t saving. The presets themselves are saving, but all of the axis and buttons I added are gone. How do I fix this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"airtrafficcontroller","CreatedById":174649,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-20T04:33:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow I didn\u0027t\u00A0see this mod before?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice choice StarMods writer and congrats Linuxgurugamer, you are\u00A0already a legend.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-20T04:33:18Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2019 04:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by airtrafficcontroller\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kennyboy","CreatedById":165397,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T16:42:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy throttle is backwards,,,, any help on how to fix this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephen Locksley","CreatedById":182846,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-03T10:32:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat! This is a good fly-by-wire mod!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cerious","CreatedById":210629,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-02T18:34:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to use my Hotas X52 in combination with BDArmory via action groups. The problem: AFBW doesn\u0027t seem to recognize a button being pressed for an extended amount of time, I can\u0027t \u0022hold\u0022 the action group.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny help would be greatly appreciated!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-02T18:50:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672684492\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cerious\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Cerious said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to use my Hotas X52 in combination with BDArmory via action groups. The problem: AFBW doesn\u0027t seem to recognize a button being pressed for an extended amount of time, I can\u0027t \u0022hold\u0022 the action group.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny help would be greatly appreciated!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wasn\u0027t aware action groups had any other state than \u0022ready to receive input\u0022. How do you hold \u0022extend solar panel\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T21:29:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672684492\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cerious\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/2/2023 at 10:34 AM, Cerious said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to use my Hotas X52 in combination with BDArmory via action groups. The problem: AFBW doesn\u0027t seem to recognize a button being pressed for an extended amount of time, I can\u0027t \u0022hold\u0022 the action group.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny help would be greatly appreciated!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe best place to ask that question would be here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3681710746\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/175359-112x-afbw-revived-joystick-controller-mod/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest of luck to you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rabbbit254","CreatedById":231293,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-21T00:52:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny way to activate controls in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003Eksc\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003Esph\u003C/abbr\u003E? Im playing on graphic tablet with controller beside me and there seems to be and issue with mouse drag to control camera anywhere in game with tablet, would help me ton in my setup to use controller in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E while building. \u0026lt;3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}